                            <comment id="17416489" author="bereng" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 06:50:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; the other PRs are up with CI that lgtm with some unrelated failures. All ok for me to commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416542" author="blerer" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 08:30:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we have a test for that validation ? If we have one it is clearly not checking the content of the error message. If we do not have one we shoud add one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416562" author="bereng" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 09:03:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No being just an error message improvement I didn&apos;t add one but I can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416602" author="bereng" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 10:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wow so I was seeing little value in testing the wording of the error message itself. But upon adding the test I found a bug in the already existing test where it was failing but for the wrong reason. Nice suggestion! Test added to PRs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
